item.title: Edgeville problem :P
item.dc:creator: @tL tL
item.description:
@tL wrote:

http://www.google.co.uk/search?q=define%3A+glitch&ie=utf-8&oe=utf-8&aq=t&rls=com.ubuntu:en-US:official&client=firefox-a

Definitions of glitch on the Web: 
* A slang term for an unexpected problem, found in either the software or hardware, which usually does not occur in a regular pattern.
  www.angelfire.com/bc/nursinginformatics/glossary2.html

* Momentary radio problem that never happens unless you are over trees or a swamp.
  www.towerhobbies.com/intros/introdictionary.html

* Synonym for bug. Often used when polygons pop out of nowhere or clip each other for no apparent reason.
  www.playstationpro2.com/dictionary.html

* A small problem or malfunction associated with a computer hardware or software, though the term has evolved to include problems in many circles.
  www.scotsmist.co.uk/glossary_g.html

* A malfunction. Glitch is sometimes used as a synonym for bug, but more often it refers to a hardware problem.
  www.angelfire.com/anime3/internet/programming.htm

* An error in the reception of a signal that creates a small error in data without affecting the transmission. For example, a glitch might make a printer print a single incorrect character.
  www.vvm.com/~jhunt/compupedia/comp_glos/g_h.htm</blockquote>

I do believe this can be classed as a glitch as it is an unexpected problem.
